de.tu_dresden.psy.inference.forms

Class AnnotableDisjunctiveNormalForm<Atoms>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tu_dresden.psy.inference.forms.AnnotableDisjunctiveNormalForm<Atoms>

  • public class AnnotableDisjunctiveNormalForm<Atoms>
extends java.lang.Object
    implements a disjunctive normal form of Atoms, i.e. a term of the form (x1_1 ^ x1_2 ^ .. ^ x1_n1) v ( ... ) ... v (xm_1 ^ xm_2 ^ .. ^ x1_nm) where every atom may be annotated as trivial. (We write a prime ' to signal this case.) A term like (m' ^ n) v (p ^ q) v (r' ^ s') may be read in context of conclusion left-hand-sides (m' ^ n) v (p ^ q) v (r' ^ s') => A means, that if p and q is stated, A follows using rules that are not marked trivial; and that if r and s is stated, A follows using rules that are marked trivial; and that if m and n is stated, A follows using both marked and unmarked rules
    Author:
    albrecht
